  "body": "### Description\n\nIn Spring reactive, there is good support for useful stack traces. Before running SpringBootApplication.run() one can insert\r\n\r\n`Hooks.onOperatorDebug();//overhead -> only dev not for production`\r\nor\r\n`ReactorDebugAgent.init();//almost no overhead -> instrumentation with checkpointing`\r\n\r\nCould be something similar added to quarkus. Currently, if an exception happens it is really hard to find where it has occurred.\r\n\r\nSee \"Reactor Debug agent - production-ready assembly back-tracing\" section under https://spring.io/blog/2019/03/28/reactor-debugging-experience\r\n\n\n### Implementation ideas\n\nSpring instruments the code by adding checkpoint on each operator\r\nhttps://projectreactor.io/docs/core/release/reference/#checkpoint-alternative",
